data.description: Enjoy ultimate convenience with the primary bedroom, living space, and kitchen seamlessly situated on the main level of this end unit villa. The kitchen is a culinary haven with a spacious island, ample cabinets, and generous counter space. Just off the kitchen, you'll find a convenient powder room, laundry room, and direct access to the garage. The kitchen seamlessly flows into the open floor plan, which encompasses the dining area and living room, creating a versatile space for both entertaining and relaxation. The living room is a cozy retreat with a gas stone fireplace, a vaulted ceiling, and easy access to the deck and backyard. Completing this level is the primary bedroom, featuring an en suite bathroom and a walk-in closet for your comfort and convenience. Moving to the upper level, you will discover three generously sized bedrooms, a full bathroom, and a bonus loft space that overlooks the living room. The loft space can serve as a home office or an additional living area. The fully finished lower level offers additional living space and includes a full bathroom with a luxurious soaking tub. It also features a workshop, ample storage, and a walk-up for easy access to the backyard. Outside, the property provides an inviting outdoor space with a trex deck, an oversized hardscape patio, and a fenced-in yard, creating an excellent area for relaxation and outdoor gatherings. The home is complete with a two-car garage and driveway space. The community offers a range of amenities, including a pool, clubhouse, walking trails, tot lots, and more. The HOA covers grass trimming and mulch, a bonus feature that simplifies your exterior maintenance. The Brunswick location provides proximity to the MARC train and commuter routes. For a full list of updates from the homeowners, please refer to the disclosures
